cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.TP, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper presents an extension of linear logic to control the complexity of functional programs with multithreading and side effects. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper introduces an extension of the call-by-value lambda calculus with multithreading and side effects. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is another possible category as the paper focuses on controlling the complexity of programs with side effects. 
- cs.TP (Theoretical Computer Science) is a possible category as the paper presents a new combinatorial proof of termination in elementary time for the functional case. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a less likely category as the paper does not focus on data structures or algorithms specifically.
